SIMPLE: mannish
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mannish
<hw>Man"nish</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Man</ets> +
<ets>-ish</ets>: cf. AS. <ets>mennisc</ets>, <ets>menisc</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Resembling a human being in form or nature;
human.</def> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>But yet it was a figure⟦br⟧
Most like to <qex>mannish</qex> creature.</q>
<rj><qau>Gower.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Resembling, suitable to, or characteristic of, a
man, manlike, masculine.</def> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A woman impudent and <qex>mannish</qex> grown.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Fond of men; -- said of a woman.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Man"nish*ly</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>,<pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Man"nish*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mannitan</ent>⟦br⟧
